gomodel:SYNGO_5151  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: Figure S2a: \"PDLIM5 is present at presynaptic terminals. Isolated chick ciliary ganglion neuron with its calyx-type presynaptic nerve terminal double stained for SV2 and PDLIM5.\"\n\nFigure S2b: \"Characterization of presynaptic membrane fractions. Synaptosomes were isolated by discontinuous sucrose g isolated by discontinuous sucrose gradient radient centrifugation and were centrifugation and were lysed by osmotic shock to generate a presynaptic membrane fraction P2\" that was enriched in three presynaptic markers: syntaxin 1, SNAP-25 and synaptotagmin. This fraction was also enriched in PDLIM5.\". Experimental description: Supplementary Figure 2 legend: \"PDLIM5 is present at presynaptic terminals. Isolated chick ciliary ganglion neuron with its calyx-type presynaptic nerve terminal double stained (Left panel) for SV2 (green) and PDLIM5\"" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date          "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_5151" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

